HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 273
BY REPRESENTATIVES CHANCE HENRY AND KNOX
A RESOLUTION
To create the Task Force on Work Release Programs to study the current administration,
efficacy, and statutory framework of work release programs administered by the
Department of Public Safety and Corrections and to provide for a written report of
its findings and recommendations to the Louisiana House of Representatives.
WHEREAS, the House of Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana recognizes
that the transition from incarceration to the community is a critical phase in reducing
recidivism and ensuring public safety; and
WHEREAS, Title 15 of the Louisiana Revised Statutes of 1950 provides the legal
framework for the rehabilitation of offenders, including specific provisions for work release
programs; and
WHEREAS, R.S. 15:711 authorizes the establishment of work release programs for
certain inmates in parish prisons or jails, while R.S. 15:1111 governs the work release
program for inmates in state correctional facilities; and
WHEREAS, multiple legislative instruments have been proposed during the 2026
Regular Session to repeal defunct or underutilized programs within the Department of Public
Safety and Corrections, indicating a legislative intent to modernize and streamline the state's
work release programming; and
WHEREAS, evidence-based research suggests that well-administered work release
programs are beneficial to the offender by providing professional skills, fostering personal
accountability, and allowing for the accumulation of savings prior to release; and
WHEREAS, such programs benefit society as a whole by increasing the likelihood
of successful reentry, reducing the long-term costs associated with recidivism, and
addressing labor needs within Louisiana's economy; and
