WHEREAS, it is a matter of significant public interest to ensure that these programs
are operating with maximum efficiency, transparency, and safety for both the participants
and the public; and
WHEREAS, a comprehensive study of the existing programs is necessary to
determine if current statutes reflect the best practices for modern correctional administration
and to identify any further legislative changes that may be needed in the future.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby create the Task Force on Work Release Programs to
study the current administration, efficacy, and statutory framework of work release programs
administered by the Department of Public Safety and Corrections and to provide for a
written report of its findings and recommendations to the Louisiana House of
Representatives no later than February 1, 2027.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall be composed of the
following members:
(1) The chairwoman of the House Committee on Administration of Criminal Justice
or her designee.
(2) One member of the Louisiana House of Representatives, appointed by the
speaker.
(3) One member of the governor's office, appointed by the governor.
(4) The secretary of the Department of Public Safety and Corrections or his
designee.
(5) The secretary of Louisiana Works or her designee.
(6) The executive director of the Louisiana Sheriffs' Association or his designee.
(7) The executive director of the Louisiana District Attorneys Association or his
designee.
(8) The president of the Louisiana District Judges Association or her designee.
(9) The director of the Drug and Specialty Court Office within the Louisiana
Supreme Court or his designee.
(10) The state director of Right on Crime or his designee.
(11) The executive director of the Louisiana Parole Project or his designee.
