(12) The president of the Louisiana Association of Business and Industry or his
designee.
(13) A representative from the Center for Employment Opportunities New Orleans.
(14) A representative from the Justice and Accountability Center of Louisiana.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the chairman and vice chairman of the task force
shall be elected by a majority of the task force members at its first meeting, which shall be
called no later than September 1, 2026, and the members may select other officers as the task
force deems appropriate.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall meet at such times and
places as determined by its chair.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that meetings of the task force may take place at the
Louisiana State Capitol, the headquarters of the Department of Public Safety and
Corrections, or any other location the chairman deems appropriate.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a majority of the task force constitutes a quorum
for the transaction of business. All official actions of the task force require the affirmative
vote of a majority of the members.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the members of the task force shall serve
without compensation, except per diem or expenses reimbursement to which they may be
individually entitled as members of their constituent organizations.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Rules of Order of the House of
Representatives or applicable Joint Rules apply to all meetings of the task force.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that meetings of the task force are subject to the
Open Meetings Law, R.S. 42:11 et seq., and records of the task force are subject to the
Public Records Law, R.S. 44:1 et seq.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall terminate following the
conclusion of its business or February 1, 2027, whichever occurs first.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Department of Public Safety and Corrections
shall provide staff support for the task force.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall submit a written report of
its findings and recommendations to the Louisiana House of Representatives no later than
February 1, 2027.
